SIMPLE: pleader
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pleader
<hw>Plead"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaideur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who pleads; one who
argues for or against; an advotate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So fair a <qex>pleader</qex> any cause may gain.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who draws up or forms pleas;
the draughtsman of pleas or pleadings in the widest sense; <as>as, a
special <ex>pleader</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleading</ent>⟦br⟧
